solutions.content:
We can use Finite State Automaton to solve the problem. The FSA contains several states and the conditions to jump between states.
Examples of states could be waiting for a digit after getting a dot, a 'E' notation or a sign, waiting for a 'e' after getting a digit etc.
The each character is what we depend on to decide how to transfer between two states.
When we traverse over the string and find out it represents a valid integer, a valid decimal or a valid 'E' notated number, which are the state 3,4,5 in the following graph, we'll return true. Otherwise return false.
![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/573a9f90-e8c3-448c-bda5-23ca530fc7cb_1631593182.6759276.jpeg)


```
class Solution {
  public boolean isNumber(String s) {
    Map<Integer, Map<String, Integer>> dfa = new HashMap();
    Map<String, Integer> state1 = new HashMap();
    state1.put("sign", 2);
    state1.put("digit", 3);
    state1.put("dot", 7);
    Map<String, Integer> state2 = new HashMap();
    state2.put("digit", 3);
    state2.put("dot", 7);
    Map<String, Integer> state3 = new HashMap();
    state3.put("digit", 3);
    state3.put("dot", 5);
    state3.put("E", 8);
    Map<String, Integer> state4 = new HashMap();
    state4.put("digit", 4);
    Map<String, Integer> state5 = new HashMap();
    state5.put("digit", 5);
    state5.put("E", 8);
    Map<String, Integer> state6 = new HashMap();
    state6.put("digit", 4);
    Map<String, Integer> state7 = new HashMap();
    state7.put("digit", 5);
    Map<String, Integer> state8 = new HashMap();
    state8.put("sign", 6);
    state8.put("digit", 4);
    dfa.put(1, state1);
    dfa.put(2, state2);
    dfa.put(3, state3);
    dfa.put(4, state4);
    dfa.put(5, state5);
    dfa.put(6, state6);
    dfa.put(7, state7);
    dfa.put(8, state8);

    Set<Integer> validStates = new HashSet(Arrays.asList(3,4,5));

    Integer state = 1;
    for (char c : s.toCharArray()) {
      String key = "";
      if (c == '+' || c == '-') {
        key = "sign";
      } else if (Character.isDigit(c)) {
        key = "digit";
      } else if (c == 'e' || c == 'E') {
        key = "E";
      } else if (c == '.') {
        key = "dot";
      }
      state = dfa.get(state).get(key);
      if (state == null) {
        return false;
      }
    }

    return validStates.contains(state);
  }
}
