### Difficulty Level
```
-> LeetCode has put the question in medium level but I would say it is you easy level .
-> Only looping and traversals techniques are using in this.
-> Good for practicing them.
-> Must suggest for beginners to try, so that they can improve skills related to looping and strings problem.
```

### Problem Statement
```
Question says we have two strings representing versions respectively.
Evaluate them and compare them whether they are equal or less than or greater than.
```

### Approach
```
Basically if we want to compare two words from dictionary and tell which come first then what we do, we just compare it characters by characters. Then whcih comes first in lexicographical order will the answer.

Similarly we are using that here.

Suppose if i say i have two versions.
V1 ->  10.8.1.0

V2 -> 10.08.1.2

Start comparing them one by one.

Step-1
V1 = 10      v2 = 10       
Equal , means they are placed in the same location of book.

Step-2
V1 = 8      V2=08
Now this would be interesting, actually they both are same we can represent '08' as '8' also so they both are same.

Step3
V1 = 1      V2=1
Again EQUAL means till now they both are same and placed at same position in dictionary.

Step4
V1 = 0      V2=2
FINALLY something different, now compare them V1<V2 means smaller one will be placed before greater one acc to dictionary rule.
So V1 will be placed before V2.
```

### SUMARRY
```
1. Check and compare each step of both the versions .
2. If the current step are same then continue your comparison.
3. If the current_step_of_V1 < current_step_of_V2 then immediately return -1 else return 1.
4. After all the comparisons , if nothing is found the return 0 they  both are same.
```
![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/591fa571-d2c0-460a-9038-e7b85e8f8fb1_1645753778.6853611.png)

### CODE

```

                               'UpVote If you are liking this daily submissions'

class Solution {
public:
    int compareVersion(string version1, string version2) 
    {

        int V1=0,V2=0,i,j,current=0;                                    //V1 for V2 for respective versions
        i=j=0;
        while(i<version1.size() || j<version2.size())
        {
            current=0;
            while(j<version2.size() && version2[j]!='.')                        //Score of version 2
            {
                current=current*10+(version2[j]-'0');
                j++;
            }
            V2+=current;
            current=0;
            while(i<version1.size() && version1[i]!='.')                         //Score of version 1
            {
                current=current*10+(version1[i]-'0');
                i++;
            }
            V1+=current;

            if(V1<V2)
                return -1;
            else if(V1>V2)
                return 1;
            i++;
            j++;
        }
        return 0;
    }
};
```

