If you don't know the math this would be really hard, so I'll explain it here. We'll be able to get Z amount of water if Z is a linear combination of X an Y. This just means that there's some equation Ax + By = Z, where A and B could be positive or negative. Think of it as filling and emptying the containers. So now we just need to determine if Z is indeed a linear combination. To do this, all we need to do is see if the GCD of X and Y is also a factor of Z. If it's not, then there's no combo we could fill up to get us to Z. 
```
class Solution {
public:
    bool canMeasureWater(int x, int y, int z) {
        if(z == 0) return true;
        if(z > x+y) return false;
        int g = gcd(x, y);
        return z % g == 0;
    }
};
