This question seems difficult at first sight but it is not. I was not able to think anything in this untill someone told me to think using **BFS**. 
So, we basically need to reach a target value using the two containers we have. What we can do is fill up one container, lets say, its capacity is j1. Now we can either empty this container(either spill the water or pour it into another container) or we can fill the another container, lets say, its capacity is j2. So, as we can see, we are having four different cases here
1. Fill the first container, ie total water we have is AlreadyFilled + j1
2. Fill the second container, ie total water we have is AlreadyFilled + j2
3. Spill the first container, ie total water we have is AlreadyFilled - j1
4. Spill the second container, ie total water we have is AlreadyFilled - j2

We see that our answer will come from a set of these operations. Now the only doubt someone can have is that how can we fill first container twice. Like, how can we do (NewFill = AlreadyFilled + j1). Then again, when in next iterations, we will have NewFill, then we will repeat these four cases and we will have NewFill + j1, ie j1 is used twice. No, its not. Actually, we can interpret it as the j1 capacity container is now poured into j2 capacity and thus j1 is empty now. So we can use j1 capacity container and hence our total filled value will thus be j1+j1. 
This way, we can put the four cases in a queue and with some base conditions, we can solve the problem.

There is another way to solve this problem which is O(1) Time and space Complexity. You can find that solution [here](https://leetcode.com/problems/water-and-jug-problem/discuss/83714/A-little-explanation-on-GCD-method.-C%2B%2BJavaPython)

```
class Solution {
public:
    bool canMeasureWater(int j1, int j2, int target) {
        if(j1+j2<target) return false;

        if(j1==target or j2==target) return true;

        unordered_map <int,int> mp;
        queue <int> q;
        q.push(0);
        while(!q.empty()){
            int filled = q.front();
            q.pop();

            if(filled == target) return true;

			// Maintaining a visited Data Structure to avoid TLE
            if(mp[filled]>0) continue;

            mp[filled] = 1;

            if(filled+j1<=j1+j2)
                q.push(filled+j1);
            if(filled-j1>=0)
                q.push(filled-j1);
            if(filled+j2<=j1+j2)
                q.push(filled+j2);
            if(filled-j2>=0)
                q.push(filled-j2);
        }
        return false;
    }
};
```

