# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
The water jug problems are always based on the ax+by linear equation. And we know that the amount of water we need as the final output is only possible if the GCD(Greatest Common Divisor) of the 2 jug capacities divides the final jug capacity fully! 

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
The basic approach to solve this problem is-
- Firstly find out the GCD and for GCD we know the Euclidean Algorithm which says that GCD of (a,b) = GCD of (a % b, b).
- This approach seems to be very likely a recursive approach to find GCD and hence we implement this using the recursion.
- After we get the GCD, we divide the target capacity with the GCD we got and if this is completely divisible by the GCD then it is possible for us to get the target value
- Lastly ensure that the target value is less than the sum of the two jug capacities.


# Code
```
class Solution {
    public boolean canMeasureWater(int jug1Capacity, int jug2Capacity, int targetCapacity) {
        if(jug1Capacity+jug2Capacity<targetCapacity){
            return false;
        }
        int a=gcd(jug1Capacity, jug2Capacity);
        if(targetCapacity%a==0){
            return true;
        }
        else{
            return false;
        }
    }
    private int gcd(int a , int b){
        if(a==0){
            return b;
        }
        return gcd(b%a, a);
    }
}
```

